questions.quote: Elaine. You don't remember our conversation? I talked about how my uncle worked in the book depository building with Lee Harvey Oswald?
Well, it still is. I shave my head for my swim team. I just liked the way it looked, so I kept it.
Ha Haaaaaaa... Jerry how do you like that.You see I get myself in a dizzy, I'm all worked up and for what?
So, I was wondering, would it be okay if I turned your room into a billiard parlor?
Under the circumstances, I don't really feel that we should be in business together.
Jerry. I don't know if you've noticed, but lately, I've been drifting, aimlessly?
Oh, well then I better get going otherwise George will make me buy him lunch to make up for that big salad he bought me yesterday.
That guy Elaine's dating seems really familiar to me. I think he may have been a comedian I worked with one time. Wait a minute, what is this?
Yeah, get this, he tells me there are no houses any where in Tuscany to rent.
I know, I know. Listen, your stuff has to be done by now, why don't you just see if it's dry?
